[2007.03.07] Pride of Tomorrow
Hyun Jun (주현준, born January 2, 1987), better known as June, is a solo R&B singer under Sony Music Japan.
His second single, "Pride of Tomorrow", was the second ending theme for the anime D. Gray-Man.
Both very popular Shonen Anime during the early 2000's.
Growing up, June was an aspiring musician.
Though not good, he was able to continue to sing until he finally made it in the music industry during his freshmen year of Highschool.
At the age of 17, June recorded a cover of Musiq's Love.
This song reached Matsuo "KC" Kiyoshi, a well-known R&B producer, who then flew to Korea to meet June.
June studied Japanese for a year to prepare, and then he made his major debut under Sony in November 2006 at the age of 19.
June also helped to arranged, composed and produced songs for Kuroki Meisa, K and South Korea actor/singer Jang Keun-suk.
It's You for anime Bleach in 2006, and following OST's like Pride of Tomorrow in 2007, You and Me in 2007, and Always in 2009.
As of 2012 June is performing in the Japanese R&B trio Wazz Up.
